What should I do on a first date?

First date? Just be *you*, man. Focus on genuinely getting to know her. Ask open-ended questions and truly listen. The best connection comes from being authentic, not from trying to impress. Let your real self shine.

"Care and effort" is right, but don't just add features. You gotta fix the bugs first. I learned that the hard way ‚Äì you can't build something lasting on a broken foundation. Get honest about what *you* need to fix before you start adding.
